<br>
<br>
*Hehe, edit:  I finally finished reading the entire thread.*<br>
<br>
<br>
1)  The druid/warrior WAS camping Sev long before he popped.  He WAS the only one (the ONLY one) in the zone several times.  No necro, no wizards... thus the &quot;the necro was camping him first&quot; theory is simply untrue.  He may have been there before the druid (maybe), but he definitely wasn't there the whole time.<br>
<br>
2)  Sev popped and was killed in a VERY short amount of time.  One or two /ooc's of Sev Camped were really all there was reasonably time for without getting reported for spam.  One does not hit hotkeys every 30 seconds.  One hits them ever few minutes.<br>
<br>
3)  VoR and friends were there incredibly quickly for a raid force.  I was very impressed with the mobility of the raid force.  VoR dropped everything to be there for the warrior, and I'm proud of them.  There was no tell to the wizards, but quite frankly, there wasn't really time for the wizards to be noticed, either.<br>
<br>
I do believe that some (I refuse to believe that ALL) of the MB'ers that came were honestly unaware of the VoR raid.  I think they thought Sev was currently uncontested.  However, by the time Sev was dead and looted, they WERE aware of the situation, and some effort at compromise SHOULD have been attempted.  The wizards are fully aware at how much advantage they have over a raid force.  Even if both had equal claim to the dragon, it's obvious who is going to get him.  No attempt at a peaceful resolution was attempted.  Not ONE item of loot was offered to the VoR people as a peace offering (not the scale, not a spell, nothing), no offers to help on the following pop (until much later).  That is what I'm most disappointed in.  Just out of respect for others, some sort of peace offering or apology, at least acknowledgement of VoR's claim, should have been made.<br>
<br>
I've always been happy with Quellious.  I have always thought that the people in general are of good quality and good character (with notable exceptions, of course).  It's this sort of thing that just disappoints me and makes me wonder if I should find somewhere else to spend my time.<br>
<br>
Sarah<br>
