They need them. In as much as ANYONE <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  needs</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> them, burners do too. They need spells they drop, hide, and guildmates need epic pieces. It's not wrong for burners to try to help their guildmates. Sorry I am just not going to buy into that nonsense. No warrior kills Sev solo. No paladin kills Gore solo. I think that's the way it <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  ought</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to work (one group only epic fights) but that's not the way it works in EQ. Everyone gets help from their guildmates to get their epics, if they can get them at all. Burners are doing exactly what they <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  should</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be doing. All epic drops that I have seen drop have gone to some guildmate that needs them or some person who camped the mob and asked burners to come help kill it. I'm sure some have been sold by burners, but I have seen them being sold long before there was MB. Some people are just lame.<br>
<br>
If you see a burner in your guild selling an epic piece you still need, then you have a right to complain. I mean WTF!<br>
<br>
But the fact is burners help guildmates get epics all the time and that's EXACTLY what they should be doing.<br>
