<br>
Why should wizards have to seek permission from anyone who just happens to be in the zone to kill a dragon?  Because they are wizards and can teleport isn't a good enough reason.  Oh yeah, I forgot, if the holy trinity isn't present, all claims to any mob or camp are null and void.  Gimme a break.  Did you know that stupid little radar system that you call a ranger or druid that you have perma camped near the spawn site to check and see when a mob is up gives your guild an advantage mana burn wizards don't have, additional time to mobilize before the 'evil empire of manaburning wizards' find out.  Instead of instantly switching characters, you could actually wait with that character and make your intent clear if it becomes an issue until others arrive.  And, oh my god, you have the presence there already to announce your guild's intentions of killing the dragon.  You're already two steps ahead of them in the courtesy line.  If they still steamroll over you, then maybe you have a legitimate gripe about being jackbooted over.  <br>
<br>
To those saying &quot;I told you so.&quot;  You didn't tell anyone anything.  It doesn't take a rocket scientist to know that manaburn can be used to killsteal, situationally, for profit.  You know, dire charm can be used to do the same thing.  Any class can kill steal.  In fact, you've yet to prove the majority of Quellious manaburn capable wizards go jackbooting over raids to line their pockets with virtual money.  A perverse side of me actually kind of wants to see an influx of wizards who use the PNP policy to their advantage that ignores raids buffing right at the tunnel in preparation for Gorenaire and goes in for the kill, then maybe you'll all realize that Quellious wizards weren't the sleazy gankers some of you try to paint them out currently to justify your jealousy.  Ultimately I know that's exactly what we all will get though and that really doesn't benefit anyone in the long run.<br>
<br>
So the manaburn team killed three Kunark dragons in one day?  Big deal, I've seen guilds kill all the Kunark dragons in the span of nine hours.  Ask Lotus Cult how long it takes them to clear NToV.<br>
<br>
If manaburn is nerfed, I hope it's followed up with nerfs to rogue assassinate ability and the monk ashenhand discipline because no class should possess the ability to kill any experience granting mob outright with a single hit, situational or not.  (And yes, at level 60, I've gotten experience from those one shot kills grouped with a rogue.)  And while they're at it, nerf the warrior defensive discipline and ranger trueshot ability, because they're all overpowered and I'm sick of listening to the whining because a few arrows actually critical hit a mob in excess of 150 points points.  And since the nerf wagon is rolling, lets add holyforge because paladins should &quot;never&quot; outdamage a warrior and unholy aura, after all its nigh unresistable.  Add charge, mighty strike, and fell strike since warriors are damage absorbers, not damage dealers and don't need any augmentation to their damage dealing abilities. <br>
<br>
As far as anyone saying six wizards does not constitute sufficient force to make a legitimate claim to take down a raid sized mob, excuse me, but who died and made you the Everquest Officiate to determine what number does or does not constitute a raid.  If a group can take down a dragon with eighteen people and another group cannot do it with less than thirty-two, how does that invalidate the capability of the eighteen people or their right to claim a mob.  The &quot;numeric&quot; requirements to raid vary from one mob to the next and can often be adjusted upwards or downwards depending on the overall raid composition based on classes, their equipment, and skill of the players.<br>
<br>
Montyy states:  &quot;this is no dif then me taking my NToV hps and AC and farming Emperor Crush in CB and only giving out Tunics to newbies I think are cool. I mean if I mobilize myself to get to crush b4 newbie group_01, then its all cool right?  I know its a dif scale, but same concept.  Farming Sucks.&quot;<br>
<br>
Those NToV hit points and armor class were not gained from farming dragonkin in ToV?  Different scale, but same concept.  Farming isn't a wonderful practice in EQ, but its become pretty much mandatory if you want anything.  Personally, I take a dimmer view of double standards.<br>
<br>
<br>
M. E.<br>
